
###################################################################################
##                                LINUX											 
###################################################################################

Steps to add this repository to your local system.

	1. Open a terminal window.

	2. Change to the directory where you want to clone this repository. For example:

		cd $FOAM_RUN

	3. Execute the following command: 
	
		$ git clone https://github.com/Alejandro-FA/pipeFlow.git


Command to create a new branch.

	$ git branch <name_of_the_new_branch>

Check how many branches are there and current branch .

	$ git branch

Command to change to another brach.

	$ git checkout <name_of_the_branch>


Steps to update local changes to GitHub (collaborators only).

	1. Stage new changes:
		All changes (including untracked files):
		$ git add -A

		All changes (only modified files, RECOMMENDED):
		$ git add -u

		Only a specific file:
		$ git add <path/to/file>

	2. Commit new changes:

		$ git commit -m "commit_message"

	3. Send new changes to remote repository (GitHub):
		
		$ git push origin <current_branch_name>


Command to discard unstaged changes (only one of them, or all of them, respectively):
	
	$ git checkout -- <path/to/file/to/revert>
	$ git checkout -- .

Command to see all new changes of the current branch:

	$ git status

Steps to merge <source_branch> to <target_branch> (<target_branch> will usually be master).

	1. Change to <target_branch> (usually master):

		$ git checkout <target_branch>

	2. See the differences before merging:
		
		$ git diff <source_branch> <target_branch>

	3. Merge changes:

		$ git merge <source_branch>


Command to delete local branch:

	$ git branch -d <branch_name>

Command to delete remote branch:

	$ git push origin --delete <branch_name>

Command to sync your local repository with GitHub (recommended to do before making any new changes).

	$ git pull origin master


